{
  "stem": "10406.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And on a certain-- certain day of the week, all the farmers that wanted to do business in town would come down with horse and wagon and park in that market area.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they would be selling their products to people in town that wanted to buy them, from fruits, to milk, and butter, and grain, and trading horses and other livestock.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived in a house.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I lived with my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And her name was Pesel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my sister, who was the oldest, her name was Blimele, [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Blime. ?] And a brother, Herschel [? or ?] [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Zvi. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And a grandmother, Bela, Bela Goldberg.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a town.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a little town--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--actually.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before the war, I was already went through Polish kindergarten and probably in first grade, started in first grade.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was like half a day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other half a day, we went for Hebrew studies.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a-- it was a a Talmud Torah, which was a combination of yeshiva-- actually, it was more of a yeshiva than-- than a Hebrew school because there was already competition between the younger modern generation, who were embracing Zionism and who wanted to learn Hebrew, in fact use Hebrew as a speaking language instead of Yiddish, which was spoken in most homes.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we would learn basically the religious aspect of Judaism there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say Orthodox was, in that town, as conservative Judaism was in this area.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody was sort of Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Although there was already a difference between the older generation that still wore beards and [? payot ?] and some of the Hasidic garb.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
